  "chain": [
    {"repo": "etcd-io/raft", "path": "raft.go", "symbol": "maybeSendSnapshot"},
    {"repo": "etcd-io/raft", "path": "log.go", "symbol": "snapshot"},
    {"repo": "etcd-io/raft", "path": "storage.go", "symbol": "Storage.Snapshot"}
  ],
  "text": "When an etcd node fails to rejoin a cluster with 'ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable', the error originates from the Raft consensus library (etcd-io/raft). The error is defined in etcd-io/raft storage.go at line 38 as: `var ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable = errors.New(\"snapshot is temporarily unavailable\")`. This error is returned by the Storage interface's Snapshot() method when a snapshot required for log catch-up is temporarily unavailable. During Raft log catch-up, when a follower node falls too far behind and needs a snapshot to rejoin the cluster, the Raft state machine calls maybeSendSnapshot() in etcd-io/raft raft.go (line 664). This function fetches the snapshot by calling raftLog.snapshot() (defined in etcd-io/raft log.go at line 291), which in turn calls the underlying Storage.Snapshot() interface method. When the Storage implementation returns ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable (checked at line 672 in raft.go), the maybeSendSnapshot function gracefully handles this by logging a debug message and returning false, allowing the Raft state machine to retry later. This mechanism allows the cluster to handle situations where a snapshot is not immediately available but may become available after giving the storage some time to prepare it, preventing the node from becoming permanently stuck during rejoin attempts."
}

